response.job_title: Software Application Engineer at Manz AG
response.summary:
I finished my bachelor in Mechatronics in September, 2018. I did an internship for Bayer as a Research assistant, developing robotic solutions for the pharmaceutical industry. Currently working as a Software Applications Engineer for the solar energy team in Manz AG.
I have a big interest in data science and machine learning.
response.skills: Programming, Robotics, Engineering, Research, Electronics, Project Management, Project Planning, Strategic Planning, Manufacturing, Troubleshooting, Product Development, Program Management, Data Analysis, Field-Programmable Gate Arrays (FPGA), Microsoft Excel, Microsoft Office, Microsoft PowerPoint, AutoCAD, Matlab, Python (Programming Language)

profile_positions.description: Development of robotic solutions for the pharmaceutical industry

company.name: Manz AG
company.description:
Manz AG is a globally active high-tech engineering company.
With a focus on the automotive industry and electromobility, battery production, electronics, energy, and medical technology, Manz develops and builds innovative and efficient production solutions: From customized single machines for laboratory production or pilot and small series production, to standardized modules and systems, to turnkey lines for mass production.
Technologically, Manz's production equipment is based on many years of experience in automation, laser processing, inspection systems, and wet chemistry.
With currently around 1,500 employees, the Manz Group develops and produces in Germany, Slovakia, Hungary, Italy, Mainland China and Taiwan. Sales and service subsidiaries also exist in the USA and India.
